OBJECTIVE OF THE POSITION: 
The Lab Assistant is anentry level position responsible for providing lab and operational supportservices to the Operations Team. This position reports to departmentsupervisor and takes direction from higher level technical personnel. 
The ideal candidate will haveexperience in working under possibly hazardous conditions (e.g. pathogens orchemicals). This individual will be well-trained to maintain safety conditionsand will be passionate for doing work that makes things move forward. 
RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Pickup, receivingand storage of clinical specimens (i.e., blood); accessioning specimens forclinical testing, making labels, setting up tubes and supplies, logging into thecomputer-based laboratory information system; inventory management support and generallab assistant type work (e.g., maintaining eye wash station, fire extinguishers,shower, stockroom, etc.). 
Asa Laboratory Assistant, this role is required to abide by applicable laws,regulations, and accreditation standards governing the Laboratory meetingqualifications under CLIA 06D2085730, Section 493.1495; Human ResourcesSustaining Standard of Practice 4 (HR Sr) Technical Personnel. 
COMPETENCY OR POSITION REQUIREMENTS: 
Compliance with immunization and other health record procedures 
Train on quality required SOPs prior to performing tasks in the laboratory 
Compliance with all laboratory safety procedures 
Ability to understand new concepts and apply them accurately 
Ability to follow detailed instructions as well as organizational policies and procedures 
Must have basic communication and interpersonal skills to enable effective interface with internal professionals 
Ability to work independently or in a team environment 
Competency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) 
